27900.content: How the sales revenue is being calculated?

27902.content: Our management software calculates the optimal order amount after you allocate the inventory to the health-centers.

27905.content: This optimal order amount is calculated by considering the length of time it takes until we receive our order, expected demand, and uncertainty in demand.

27907.content: We will make $5 for each unit of {drugName} that we sell, but there is a cost of $1 for each unit of inventory and a cost of $10 for each unit of backlog which is the demand we cannot satisfy.

For Ordering Order-up-to-level: As calculated by the management system, this accounts for the length of time it takes until you receive your order, expected demand, and uncertainty in demand.
